description: {"blocks":[{"key":"cvrn4","text":"Protocol for microscopy-based mitochondrial morphology measurements in iNeurons","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2279u","text":"Day 0: Treat AAVS1-TRE3G-NGN2 cells with Accutase and plate the dissociated cells in matrigel-coated 6-well plates (2x105 cells/well) in ND1 Medium supplemented with Y27632 (10 μM).  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aj5cj","text":"ND1 Medium:  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3s3eb","text":"DMEM/F12 ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2n05","text":"N2 (100x)        1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7cd70","text":"BDNF              10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3u5r0","text":"NT3                 10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6jcn0","text":"NEAA (100X) 1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9uejb","text":"Laminin           0.2 μg/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4jegl","text":"Doxycycline    2 μg/ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8nnac","text":"Day 1: Replace the medium with ND1 Medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bec7a","text":"Day 2: Replace the medium with ND2 Medium.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6k6h7","text":"ND2 Medium  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bc0kf","text":"Neurobasal medium  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1kfdt","text":"B27 (50x)                    1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f05l8","text":"GlutaMax (100x)         1x  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2nni5","text":"BDNF                          10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9fbik","text":"NT3                             10 ng/ml  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"44dbl","text":"Doxycycline                2 μg/ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"59amj","text":"Day 4: Exchange 50% of the medium from each well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f686d","text":"Day 6: Treat the cells with Accutase and replate the dissociated cells in matrigel-coated  6-/12-well glass bottom plates (2-4x105 cells/well for 6 wells) in ND2 Medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7re5r","text":"Day 8 and thereafter: Exchange 50% of the medium from each well every other day.  ·      ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"be85u","text":"Doxycycline can be withdrawn on Day.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8jljt","text":"Induce mitophagy using Antimycin A / Oligomycin A for the desired time. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8qr3h","text":"Aspirate medium and fix cells in 1 ml pre-warmed 4% PFA for 30 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eo2mb","text":"Aspirate PFA solution and wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"517fu","text":"Permeabilize the cells by adding 0.2% Triton X-100 in PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"34l9g","text":"Remove the detergent solution by aspiration.  Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e7p4d","text":"Block cells for 10 min with 3% BSA – 1x PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5ifer","text":"Remove BSA solution by aspiration.  Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3o1ds","text":"Incubate with primary antibodies in 3% BSA - 1x PBS for 3h at RT with gentle shaking.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e8206","text":"a.     Anti-HSP60 (mouse)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fbotc","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5tcbh","text":"Incubate with secondary antibodies in 3% BSA - 1x PBS for 45 min – 1h.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cbaeu","text":"b.     Goat anti-mouse AlexaFlour 488","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"71l9s","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"hgd8","text":"Add Hoechst33342 or DAPI 1:2000 to wells for 5 min with gentle shaking.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9b1tb","text":"Wash wells 3x with PBST (1x PBS, 0.02% Tween 20). Drain well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f7kdu","text":"Exchange PBST with 1x PBS and keep cells at 4°C until imaging. Image within the next few days.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b5n65","text":"Mount glass bottom plate on Yokogawa CSU-W1 spinning disk confocal on a Nikon Eclipse Ti-E motorized microscope equipped with a Nikon Apochromat 60×/1.42 N.A oil-objective lens. Image signals of 488/568/647 fluorophores in sequential manner with a Nikon LUN-F XL solid state laser combiner ([laser line – laser power]: 488 - 80mW, 561 - 65mW, 640nm - 60mW]) using a Semrock Di01-T405/488/568/647 dichroic mirror. Fluorescence emissions were collected with 488 Chroma ET525/50m [488 nm], 568 Chroma ET605/52m [561 nm], 633 Chroma ET705/72m [640 nm] filters, respectively (Chroma Technologies) using NIS-Elements image acquisition software. Consistent laser intensity and exposure times must be maintained for all samples. Acquire 8 µm z-stacks for each image.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2q7r4","text":"Image adequate number of cells per repeat in each condition. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ab9rn","text":"Perform image quantification was in your tool of choice. Here we will use ImageJ/FiJi and custom-written batch-macros (https://github.com/harperlaboratory/FBXO7).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dbrvq","text":"Count number of nuclei for normalization.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fghqf","text":"Plot results in your tool of choice for graphing and statistical analysis.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
